hip_device_properties.computeModeDescription: Default (multiple host threads can use ::hipSetDevice() with device simultaneously)

OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_BACKEND.name: causal_backend
OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_BACKEND.description: Backend for call-stack sampling. See https://amdresearch.github.io/omnitrace/causal_profiling.html#backends for more info. If set to "auto", omnitrace will attempt to use the perf backend and fallback on the timer backend if unavailable

OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_BINARY_EXCLUDE.name: causal_binary_exclude
OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_BINARY_EXCLUDE.description: Excludes binaries matching the list of provided regexes from causal experiments (separated by tab, semi-colon, and/or quotes (single or double))

OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_BINARY_SCOPE.name: causal_binary_scope
OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_BINARY_SCOPE.description: Limits causal experiments to the binaries matching the provided list of regular expressions (separated by tab, semi-colon, and/or quotes (single or double))

OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_DELAY.name: causal_delay
OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_DELAY.description: Length of time to wait (in seconds) before starting the first causal experiment

OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_DURATION.name: causal_duration
OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_DURATION.description: Length of time to perform causal experimentation (in seconds) after the first experiment has started. After this amount of time has elapsed, no more causal experiments will be performed and the application will continue without any overhead from causal profiling. Any value <= 0 means until the application completes

OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_END_TO_END.name: causal_end_to_end
OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_END_TO_END.description: Perform causal experiment over the length of the entire application

OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_FILE.name: causal_file
OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_FILE.description: Name of causal output filename (w/o extension)

OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_FILE_RESET.name: causal_file_reset
OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_FILE_RESET.description: Overwrite any existing causal output file instead of appending to it

OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_FIXED_SPEEDUP.name: causal_fixed_speedup
OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_FIXED_SPEEDUP.description: List of virtual speedups between 0 and 100 (inclusive) to sample from for causal profiling

OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_FUNCTION_EXCLUDE.name: causal_function_exclude
OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_FUNCTION_EXCLUDE.description: Excludes functions matching the list of provided regexes from causal experiments (separated by tab, semi-colon, and/or quotes (single or double))

OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_FUNCTION_EXCLUDE_DEFAUL.name: causal_function_exclude_defaults
OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_FUNCTION_EXCLUDE_DEFAUL.description: This controls adding a series of function exclude regexes to avoid experimenting on STL implementation functions, etc. which are, generally, not helpful. Details: excludes demangled function names starting with '_' or containing '::_M'.

OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_FUNCTION_SCOPE.name: causal_function_scope
OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_FUNCTION_SCOPE.description: List of <function> regex entries for causal profiling (separated by tab, semi-colon, and/or quotes (single or double))

OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_MODE.name: causal_mode
OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_MODE.description: Perform causal experiments at the function-scope or line-scope. Ideally, use function first to locate function with highest impact and then switch to line mode + OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_FUNCTION_SCOPE set to the function being targeted.

OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_RANDOM_SEED.name: causal_random_seed
OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_RANDOM_SEED.description: Seed for random number generator which selects speedups and experiments -- please note that the lines selected for experimentation are not reproducible but the speedup selection is. If set to zero, std::random_device{}() will be used.

OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_SOURCE_EXCLUDE.name: causal_source_exclude
OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_SOURCE_EXCLUDE.description: Excludes source files or source file + lineno pair (i.e. <file> or <file>:<line>) matching the list of provided regexes from causal experiments (separated by tab, semi-colon, and/or quotes (single or double))

OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_SOURCE_SCOPE.name: causal_source_scope
OMNITRACE_CAUSAL_SOURCE_SCOPE.description: Limits causal experiments to the source files or source file + lineno pair (i.e. <file> or <file>:<line>) matching the provided list of regular expressions (separated by tab, semi-colon, and/or quotes (single or double))

OMNITRACE_CI.name: ci
OMNITRACE_CI.description: Enable some runtime validation checks (typically enabled for continuous integration)

OMNITRACE_CRITICAL_TRACE.name: critical_trace
OMNITRACE_CRITICAL_TRACE.description: Enable generation of the critical trace

OMNITRACE_CRITICAL_TRACE_BUFFER_COUNT.name: critical_trace_buffer_count
OMNITRACE_CRITICAL_TRACE_BUFFER_COUNT.description: Number of critical trace records to store in thread-local memory before submitting to shared buffer

OMNITRACE_CRITICAL_TRACE_COUNT.name: critical_trace_count
OMNITRACE_CRITICAL_TRACE_COUNT.description: Number of critical trace to export (0 == all)

OMNITRACE_CRITICAL_TRACE_PER_ROW.name: critical_trace_per_row
OMNITRACE_CRITICAL_TRACE_PER_ROW.description: How many critical traces per row in perfetto (0 == all in one row)

OMNITRACE_CRITICAL_TRACE_SERIALIZE_NAMES.name: critical_trace_serialize_names
OMNITRACE_CRITICAL_TRACE_SERIALIZE_NAMES.description: Include names in serialization of critical trace (mainly for debugging)

OMNITRACE_DIFF_OUTPUT.name: diff_output
OMNITRACE_DIFF_OUTPUT.description: Generate a difference output vs. a pre-existing output (see also: INPUT_PATH and INPUT_PREFIX)

OMNITRACE_DISABLE_CATEGORIES.name: disable_categories
OMNITRACE_DISABLE_CATEGORIES.description: Disable collecting profiling and trace data for these categories

OMNITRACE_ENABLE_CATEGORIES.name: enable_categories
OMNITRACE_ENABLE_CATEGORIES.description: Enable collecting profiling and trace data for these categories and disable all other categories

OMNITRACE_FLAT_PROFILE.name: flat_profile
OMNITRACE_FLAT_PROFILE.description: Set the label hierarchy mode to default to flat

OMNITRACE_INPUT_EXTENSIONS.name: input_extensions
OMNITRACE_INPUT_EXTENSIONS.description: File extensions used when searching for input files used in difference comparisons (see also: DIFF_OUTPUT)

OMNITRACE_INPUT_PATH.name: input_path
OMNITRACE_INPUT_PATH.description: Explicitly specify the input folder for difference comparisons (see also: DIFF_OUTPUT)

OMNITRACE_INPUT_PREFIX.name: input_prefix
OMNITRACE_INPUT_PREFIX.description: Explicitly specify the prefix for input files used in difference comparisons (see also: DIFF_OUTPUT)

OMNITRACE_KOKKOSP_DEEP_COPY.name: kokkosp_deep_copy
OMNITRACE_KOKKOSP_DEEP_COPY.description: Enable tracking deep copies (warning: may corrupt flamegraph in perfetto)

OMNITRACE_KOKKOSP_NAME_LENGTH_MAX.name: kokkosp_name_length_max
OMNITRACE_KOKKOSP_NAME_LENGTH_MAX.description: Set this to a value > 0 to help avoid unnamed Kokkos Tools callbacks. Generally, unnamed callbacks are the demangled name of the function, which is very long

OMNITRACE_KOKKOSP_PREFIX.name: kokkosp_prefix
OMNITRACE_KOKKOSP_PREFIX.description: Set to [kokkos] to maintain old naming convention

OMNITRACE_MAX_DEPTH.name: max_depth
OMNITRACE_MAX_DEPTH.description: Set the maximum depth of label hierarchy reporting

OMNITRACE_MAX_WIDTH.name: max_width
OMNITRACE_MAX_WIDTH.description: Set the maximum width for component label outputs

OMNITRACE_MEMORY_PRECISION.name: memory_precision
OMNITRACE_MEMORY_PRECISION.description: Set the precision for components with 'is_memory_category' type-trait

OMNITRACE_MEMORY_SCIENTIFIC.name: memory_scientific
OMNITRACE_MEMORY_SCIENTIFIC.description: Set the numerical reporting format for components with 'is_memory_category' type-trait

OMNITRACE_MEMORY_UNITS.name: memory_units
OMNITRACE_MEMORY_UNITS.description: Set the units for components with 'uses_memory_units' type-trait

OMNITRACE_MEMORY_WIDTH.name: memory_width
OMNITRACE_MEMORY_WIDTH.description: Set the output width for components with 'is_memory_category' type-trait

OMNITRACE_MODE.name: mode
OMNITRACE_MODE.description: Data collection mode. Used to set default values for OMNITRACE_USE_* options. Typically set by omnitrace binary instrumenter.

OMNITRACE_NODE_COUNT.name: node_count
OMNITRACE_NODE_COUNT.description: Total number of nodes used in application. Setting this value > 1 will result in aggregating N processes into groups of N / NODE_COUNT

OMNITRACE_NUM_THREADS_HINT.name: num_threads_hint
OMNITRACE_NUM_THREADS_HINT.description: This is hint for how many threads are expected to be created in the application. Setting this value allows omnitrace to preallocate resources during initialization and warn about any potential issues. For example, when call-stack sampling, each thread has a unique sampler instance which communicates with an allocator instance running in a background thread. Each allocator only handles N sampling instances (where N is the value of OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_ALLOCATOR_SIZE). When this hint is set to >= the number of threads that get sampled, omnitrace can start all the background threads during initialization

OMNITRACE_OUTPUT_PATH.name: output_path
OMNITRACE_OUTPUT_PATH.description: Explicitly specify the output folder for results

OMNITRACE_OUTPUT_PREFIX.name: output_prefix
OMNITRACE_OUTPUT_PREFIX.description: Explicitly specify a prefix for all output files

OMNITRACE_PAPI_EVENTS.name: papi_events
OMNITRACE_PAPI_EVENTS.description: PAPI presets and events to collect (see also: papi_avail)

OMNITRACE_PAPI_FAIL_ON_ERROR.name: papi_fail_on_error
OMNITRACE_PAPI_FAIL_ON_ERROR.description: Configure PAPI errors to trigger a runtime error

OMNITRACE_PAPI_OVERFLOW.name: papi_overflow
OMNITRACE_PAPI_OVERFLOW.description: Value at which PAPI hw counters trigger an overflow callback

OMNITRACE_PAPI_QUIET.name: papi_quiet
OMNITRACE_PAPI_QUIET.description: Configure suppression of reporting PAPI errors/warnings

OMNITRACE_PAPI_THREADING.name: papi_threading
OMNITRACE_PAPI_THREADING.description: Enable multithreading support when using PAPI

OMNITRACE_PERFETTO_ANNOTATIONS.name: perfetto_annotations
OMNITRACE_PERFETTO_ANNOTATIONS.description: Include debug annotations in perfetto trace. When enabled, this feature will encode information such as the values of the function arguments (when available). Disabling this feature may dramatically reduce the size of the trace

OMNITRACE_PERFETTO_BACKEND.name: perfetto_backend
OMNITRACE_PERFETTO_BACKEND.description: Specify the perfetto backend to activate. Options are: 'inprocess', 'system', or 'all'

OMNITRACE_PERFETTO_COMPACT_ROCTRACER_ANN.name: perfetto_compact_roctracer_annotations
OMNITRACE_PERFETTO_COMPACT_ROCTRACER_ANN.description: When PERFETTO_ANNOTATIONS, USE_ROCTRACER, and ROCTRACER_HIP_API are all enabled, enabling this option will result in the arg information for HIP API calls to all be within one annotation (e.g., args="stream=0x0, dst=0x1F, sizeBytes=64, src=0x08, kind=1"). When disabled, each parameter will be an individual annotation (e.g. stream, dst, sizeBytes, etc.). The benefit of the former is that it is faster to serialize and consumes less file space; the benefit of the latter is that it becomes much easier to find slices in the trace with the same value

OMNITRACE_PERFETTO_FILL_POLICY.name: perfetto_fill_policy
OMNITRACE_PERFETTO_FILL_POLICY.description: Behavior when perfetto buffer is full. 'discard' will ignore new entries, 'ring_buffer' will overwrite old entries

OMNITRACE_PERFETTO_ROCTRACER_PER_STREAM.name: perfetto_roctracer_per_stream
OMNITRACE_PERFETTO_ROCTRACER_PER_STREAM.description: Separate roctracer GPU side traces (copies, kernels) into separate tracks based on the stream they're enqueued into

OMNITRACE_PERFETTO_SHMEM_SIZE_HINT_KB.name: perfetto_shmem_size_hint_kb
OMNITRACE_PERFETTO_SHMEM_SIZE_HINT_KB.description: Hint for shared-memory buffer size in perfetto (in KB)

OMNITRACE_PRECISION.name: precision
OMNITRACE_PRECISION.description: Set the global output precision for components

OMNITRACE_PROCESS_SAMPLING_DURATION.name: process_sampling_duration
OMNITRACE_PROCESS_SAMPLING_DURATION.description: If > 0.0, time (in seconds) to sample before stopping. If less than zero, uses OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_DURATION

OMNITRACE_PROCESS_SAMPLING_FREQ.name: process_sampling_freq
OMNITRACE_PROCESS_SAMPLING_FREQ.description: Number of measurements per second when OMNITTRACE_USE_PROCESS_SAMPLING=ON. If set to zero, uses OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_FREQ value

OMNITRACE_ROCM_EVENTS.name: rocm_events
OMNITRACE_ROCM_EVENTS.description: ROCm hardware counters. Use ':device=N' syntax to specify collection on device number N, e.g. ':device=0'. If no device specification is provided, the event is collected on every available device

OMNITRACE_ROCM_SMI_METRICS.name: rocm_smi_metrics
OMNITRACE_ROCM_SMI_METRICS.description: rocm-smi metrics to collect: busy, temp, power, mem_usage

OMNITRACE_ROCTRACER_DISCARD_BARRIERS.name: roctracer_discard_barriers
OMNITRACE_ROCTRACER_DISCARD_BARRIERS.description: Skip barrier marker events in traces

OMNITRACE_ROCTRACER_HIP_API_BACKTRACE.name: roctracer_hip_api_backtrace
OMNITRACE_ROCTRACER_HIP_API_BACKTRACE.description: Enable annotating the perfetto debug annotation with backtraces

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_ALLOCATOR_SIZE.name: sampling_allocator_size
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_ALLOCATOR_SIZE.description: The number of sampled threads handled by an allocator running in a background thread. Each thread that is sampled communicates with an allocator running in a background thread which handles storing/caching the data when it's buffer is full. Setting this value too high (i.e. equal to the number of threads when the thread count is high) may cause loss of data -- the sampler may fill a new buffer and overwrite old buffer data before the allocator can process it. Setting this value to 1 will result in a background allocator thread for every thread started by the application.

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_CPUS.name: sampling_cpus
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_CPUS.description: CPUs to collect frequency information for. Values should be separated by commas and can be explicit or ranges, e.g. 0,1,5-8. An empty value implies 'all' and 'none' suppresses all CPU frequency sampling

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_CPUTIME.name: sampling_cputime
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_CPUTIME.description: Enable sampling frequency via a timer that measures both CPU time used by the current process, and CPU time expended on behalf of the process by the system. This is recommended.

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_CPUTIME_DELAY.name: sampling_cputime_delay
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_CPUTIME_DELAY.description: Time (in seconds) to wait before the first CPU-time sampling signal is delivered. Defaults to OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_DELAY when <= 0.0

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_CPUTIME_FREQ.name: sampling_cputime_freq
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_CPUTIME_FREQ.description: Number of software interrupts per second of CPU-time. Defaults to OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_FREQ when <= 0.0

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_CPUTIME_SIGNAL.name: sampling_cputime_signal
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_CPUTIME_SIGNAL.description: Modify this value only if the target process is also using the same signal (SIGPROF)

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_CPUTIME_TIDS.name: sampling_cputime_tids
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_CPUTIME_TIDS.description: Same as OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_TIDS but applies specifically to samplers whose timers are based on the CPU-time. This is useful when you want to restrict samples to particular threads.

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_DELAY.name: sampling_delay
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_DELAY.description: Time (in seconds) to wait before the first sampling signal is delivered, increasing this value can fix deadlocks during init

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_DURATION.name: sampling_duration
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_DURATION.description: If > 0.0, time (in seconds) to sample before stopping

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_FREQ.name: sampling_freq
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_FREQ.description: Number of software interrupts per second when OMNITTRACE_USE_SAMPLING=ON

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_GPUS.name: sampling_gpus
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_GPUS.description: Devices to query when OMNITRACE_USE_ROCM_SMI=ON. Values should be separated by commas and can be explicit or ranges, e.g. 0,1,5-8. An empty value implies 'all' and 'none' suppresses all GPU sampling

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_INCLUDE_INLINES.name: sampling_include_inlines
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_INCLUDE_INLINES.description: Create entries for inlined functions when available

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_KEEP_INTERNAL.name: sampling_keep_internal
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_KEEP_INTERNAL.description: Configure whether the statistical samples should include call-stack entries from internal routines in omnitrace. E.g. when ON, the call-stack will show functions like omnitrace_push_trace. If disabled, omnitrace will attempt to filter out internal routines from the sampling call-stacks

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_OVERFLOW.name: sampling_overflow
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_OVERFLOW.description: Enable sampling via an overflow of a HW counter. This requires Linux perf (/proc/sys/kernel/perf_event_paranoid created by OS) with a value of 2 or less in that file

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_OVERFLOW_FREQ.name: sampling_overflow_freq
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_OVERFLOW_FREQ.description: Number of events in between each sample. Defaults to OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_FREQ when <= 0.0

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_OVERFLOW_SIGNAL.name: sampling_overflow_signal
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_OVERFLOW_SIGNAL.description: Modify this value only if the target process is also using the same signal (SIGRTMIN + 1)

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_OVERFLOW_TIDS.name: sampling_overflow_tids
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_OVERFLOW_TIDS.description: Same as OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_TIDS but applies specifically to samplers whose samples are based on the overflow of a particular event. This is useful when you want to restrict samples to particular threads.

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_REALTIME.name: sampling_realtime
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_REALTIME.description: Enable sampling frequency via a wall-clock timer. This may result in typically idle child threads consuming an unnecessary large amount of CPU time.

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_REALTIME_DELAY.name: sampling_realtime_delay
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_REALTIME_DELAY.description: Time (in seconds) to wait before the first real (wall) time sampling signal is delivered. Defaults to OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_DELAY when <= 0.0

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_REALTIME_FREQ.name: sampling_realtime_freq
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_REALTIME_FREQ.description: Number of software interrupts per second of real (wall) time. Defaults to OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_FREQ when <= 0.0

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_REALTIME_SIGNAL.name: sampling_realtime_signal
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_REALTIME_SIGNAL.description: Modify this value only if the target process is also using the same signal (SIGRTMIN)

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_REALTIME_TIDS.name: sampling_realtime_tids
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_REALTIME_TIDS.description: Same as OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_TIDS but applies specifically to samplers whose timers are based on the real (wall) time. This is useful when you want to restrict samples to particular threads.

OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_TIDS.name: sampling_tids
OMNITRACE_SAMPLING_TIDS.description: Limit call-stack sampling to specific thread IDs, starting at zero for the main thread. Be aware that some libraries, such as ROCm may create additional threads which increment the TID count. However, no threads started by omnitrace will increment the TID count. Values should be separated by commas and can be explicit or ranges, e.g. 0,1,5-8. An empty value implies all TIDs.

OMNITRACE_SCIENTIFIC.name: scientific
OMNITRACE_SCIENTIFIC.description: Set the global numerical reporting to scientific format

OMNITRACE_STRICT_CONFIG.name: strict_config
OMNITRACE_STRICT_CONFIG.description: Throw errors for unknown setting names in configuration files instead of emitting a warning

OMNITRACE_SUPPRESS_CONFIG.name: suppress_config
OMNITRACE_SUPPRESS_CONFIG.description: Disable processing of setting configuration files

OMNITRACE_THREAD_POOL_SIZE.name: thread_pool_size
OMNITRACE_THREAD_POOL_SIZE.description: Max number of threads for processing background tasks

OMNITRACE_TIMELINE_PROFILE.name: timeline_profile
OMNITRACE_TIMELINE_PROFILE.description: Set the label hierarchy mode to default to timeline

OMNITRACE_TIMEMORY_COMPONENTS.name: timemory_components
OMNITRACE_TIMEMORY_COMPONENTS.description: List of components to collect via timemory (see `omnitrace-avail -C`)

OMNITRACE_TIME_FORMAT.name: time_format
OMNITRACE_TIME_FORMAT.description: Customize the folder generation when TIME_OUTPUT is enabled (see also: strftime)

OMNITRACE_TIME_OUTPUT.name: time_output
OMNITRACE_TIME_OUTPUT.description: Output data to subfolder w/ a timestamp (see also: TIME_FORMAT)

OMNITRACE_TIMING_PRECISION.name: timing_precision
OMNITRACE_TIMING_PRECISION.description: Set the precision for components with 'is_timing_category' type-trait

OMNITRACE_TIMING_SCIENTIFIC.name: timing_scientific
OMNITRACE_TIMING_SCIENTIFIC.description: Set the numerical reporting format for components with 'is_timing_category' type-trait

OMNITRACE_TIMING_UNITS.name: timing_units
OMNITRACE_TIMING_UNITS.description: Set the units for components with 'uses_timing_units' type-trait

OMNITRACE_TIMING_WIDTH.name: timing_width
OMNITRACE_TIMING_WIDTH.description: Set the output width for components with 'is_timing_category' type-trait

OMNITRACE_TRACE_DELAY.name: trace_delay
OMNITRACE_TRACE_DELAY.description: Time in seconds to wait before enabling trace/profile data collection. If multiple delays + durations are needed, see OMNITRACE_TRACE_PERIODS.

OMNITRACE_TRACE_DURATION.name: trace_duration
OMNITRACE_TRACE_DURATION.description: If > 0.0, time (in seconds) to collect trace/profile data. If multiple delays + durations are needed, see OMNITRACE_TRACE_PERIODS.

OMNITRACE_TRACE_PERIODS.name: trace_periods
OMNITRACE_TRACE_PERIODS.description: Similar to specify trace delay and/or duration except in the form <DELAY>:<DURATION>, <DELAY>:<DURATION>:<REPEAT>, and/or <DELAY>:<DURATION>:<REPEAT>:<CLOCK_ID>

OMNITRACE_TRACE_PERIOD_CLOCK_ID.name: trace_period_clock_id
OMNITRACE_TRACE_PERIOD_CLOCK_ID.description: Set the default clock ID for OMNITRACE_TRACE_DELAY, OMNITRACE_TRACE_DURATION, and/or OMNITRACE_TRACE_PERIODS. E.g. "realtime" == the delay/duration is governed by the elapsed realtime, "cputime" == the delay/duration is governed by the elapsed CPU-time within the process, etc. Note: when using CPU-based timing, it is recommened to scale the value by the number of threads and be aware that omnitrace may contribute to advancing the process CPU-time

OMNITRACE_TRACE_THREAD_BARRIERS.name: trace_thread_barriers
OMNITRACE_TRACE_THREAD_BARRIERS.description: Enable tracing calls to pthread_barrier functions.

OMNITRACE_TRACE_THREAD_JOIN.name: trace_thread_join
OMNITRACE_TRACE_THREAD_JOIN.description: Enable tracing calls to pthread_join functions.

OMNITRACE_TRACE_THREAD_LOCKS.name: trace_thread_locks
OMNITRACE_TRACE_THREAD_LOCKS.description: Enable tracing calls to pthread_mutex_lock, pthread_mutex_unlock, pthread_mutex_trylock

OMNITRACE_TRACE_THREAD_RW_LOCKS.name: trace_thread_rw_locks
OMNITRACE_TRACE_THREAD_RW_LOCKS.description: Enable tracing calls to pthread_rwlock_* functions. May cause deadlocks with ROCm-enabled OpenMPI.

OMNITRACE_TRACE_THREAD_SPIN_LOCKS.name: trace_thread_spin_locks
OMNITRACE_TRACE_THREAD_SPIN_LOCKS.description: Enable tracing calls to pthread_spin_* functions. May cause deadlocks with MPI distributions.

OMNITRACE_USE_PID.name: use_pid
OMNITRACE_USE_PID.description: Enable tagging filenames with process identifier (either MPI rank or pid)

OMNITRACE_USE_PROCESS_SAMPLING.name: use_process_sampling
OMNITRACE_USE_PROCESS_SAMPLING.description: Enable a background thread which samples process-level and system metrics such as the CPU/GPU freq, power, memory usage, etc.

OMNITRACE_USE_RCCLP.name: use_rcclp
OMNITRACE_USE_RCCLP.description: Enable support for ROCm Communication Collectives Library (RCCL) Performance

OMNITRACE_USE_ROCM_SMI.name: use_rocm_smi
OMNITRACE_USE_ROCM_SMI.description: Enable sampling GPU power, temp, utilization, and memory usage

OMNITRACE_USE_ROCTRACER.name: use_roctracer
OMNITRACE_USE_ROCTRACER.description: Enable ROCm API and kernel tracing

OMNITRACE_USE_ROCTX.name: use_roctx
OMNITRACE_USE_ROCTX.description: Enable ROCtx API. Warning! Out-of-order ranges may corrupt perfetto flamegraph

OMNITRACE_USE_TEMPORARY_FILES.name: use_temporary_files
OMNITRACE_USE_TEMPORARY_FILES.description: Write data to temporary files to minimize the memory usage of omnitrace, e.g. call-stack samples will be periodically written to a file and re-loaded during finalization

OMNITRACE_WIDTH.name: width
OMNITRACE_WIDTH.description: Set the global output width for components
